{
  "texts": [
    "By contrast, LoRAPrune [85] jointly pruning LoRA matrices and the LLM parameters based on LoRA's gradients.",
    "Besides, we can also use LoRA to support parameters pruning for LLMs [86,87].",
    "Parameter sharingParameter-sharing methods reduce the number of parameters by sharing parameters across different layers or modules of LLMs.",
    "VeRA [88] and VB-LoRA [89] are two representative parameter-sharing methods for LoRA.",
    "Specifically, VeRA proposes to share a pair of frozen random matrices across all layers and conduct layer-wise adaptation with \"scaling vectors\"."
  ]
}